# Mitch Colvin

**Mitch Colvin** (born 1973) is an American businessman, [mortician](/Mortician), and politician who has served as the [Mayor of Fayetteville, North Carolina](/Mayor_of_Fayetteville,_North_Carolina) since December 2017. A member of the [Democratic Party](/Democratic_Party_(United_States)), Colvin has been a prominent figure in Fayetteville's political landscape, known for his leadership and community engagement.

## Early Life and Education

Mitch Colvin was born in 1973 in [Fayetteville, North Carolina](/Fayetteville,_North_Carolina). He attended [Fayetteville State University](/Fayetteville_State_University), where he honed his skills and prepared for a career in public service. His educational background has played a significant role in shaping his political career and community involvement.

## Political Career

### Fayetteville City Council

Colvin's political career began when he was elected to the Fayetteville City Council, serving two consecutive terms from 2013 to 2017. During his tenure on the council, he was known for his dedication to community issues and his ability to work across party lines to achieve common goals.

### Mayor of Fayetteville

In July 2017, Colvin filed as a candidate for the office of Mayor of Fayetteville. He led all candidates in the primary election held in October 2017, securing 45% of the votes. In the general election held in November 2017, Colvin faced incumbent [Nat Robertson](/Nat_Robertson), a Republican, and won with 59% of the vote.

Colvin's tenure as mayor has been marked by significant achievements, including the negotiation of a deal to bring a minor league baseball affiliate of the [Houston Astros](/Houston_Astros) to downtown Fayetteville. This effort resulted in the establishment of the [Fayetteville Woodpeckers](/Fayetteville_Woodpeckers), a minor league team that has become a source of pride for the community.

### Re-elections

In the [November 2019 election](/2019_Fayetteville,_North_Carolina,_mayoral_election), Colvin was the only candidate on the ballot, receiving an overwhelming 95% of the vote. He was re-elected in [2022](/2022_Fayetteville,_North_Carolina,_mayoral_election) with 62% of the vote, demonstrating his continued popularity and effectiveness as a leader.

## Community Involvement

In addition to his political roles, Colvin has been actively involved in various community initiatives. In May 2017, [North Carolina Governor](/Governor_of_North_Carolina) [Roy Cooper](/Roy_Cooper) appointed Colvin to the Governor's Crime Commission. He began his work on the Commission during its June 2017 quarterly meeting, contributing to efforts aimed at reducing crime and improving public safety in North Carolina.

## Personal Life

Colvin is also a licensed [mortician](/Mortician), a profession that has given him a unique perspective on community service and the importance of compassion and empathy. His dual roles as a businessman and a public servant have allowed him to make significant contributions to the Fayetteville community.